## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent complexity of international trade dynamics. The perspectives presented are based on existing literature and may not capture all nuances of the debate. Additionally, the interpretation of whether agencies prevent or promote free trade can vary depending on the specific practices and policies in question.

